What is virtual reality? (VR)
The difference of VR to other gaming systems.

VR for console
Creation date start 11/28/20 finish 12/6/20 Made by Zachary wise for college project.
With the enhanced capabilities that a high end computer’s hardware provides, virtual reality can do more here than anywhere else. High quality immersive games use the most of what pcs provide, games like Half-Life Alyx which couldn’t run on a console due to the amount of power they need to show the environment in high levels of detail. It’s not only the games however, the vr equipment itself is more accurate and complex than its console counterparts. Some even going as far as to being entirely self-contained, meaning you have free movement without the hassle of cords.
The power provided by all of this gives even the players to enhance their own experience, modders especially have taken storm using all of what’s capable with a pc to make games more then what they originally were.
However vr on pc is not only for games, even if that’s the main focus currently vr is being experimented with in many ways for many fields, including medical, space and science, and even the military. As of now however vr is mainly used for entertainment.
All of these pieces placed together makes pc and more advanced but also more committed place to experience virtual reality, with better gar but also a larger price tag
Half-life Alyx is an immersive virtual reality experience, being one of the more demanding yet visually stunning games. Providing an immersive game that rivals any book, show, or game. Winning multiple rewards and being a key point in the power of vr.
